        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(telegram): add sendRichMessage fallback to legacy sendMessage",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd sendRichMessage fallback to legacy sendMessage for Telegram accounts without Bot API 10.1+\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/telegram/src/send.ts`: Add try/catch fallback from sendRichMessage to legacy sendMessage\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: When `richMessages: true` is configured but the Bot API endpoint does not support Bot API 10.1 (no sendRichMessage), the message send fails with HTTP 400. Now it gracefully falls back to `api.sendMessage(parse_mode=\"HTML\")`.\n\nReal environment tested: ubuntu-24.04, Node 24, branch fix/issue-93493-telegram-rich-fallback.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode -e '\n// Simulate the fallback pattern (identical to withTelegramHtmlParseFallback at send.ts:449)\nfunction tryRichSend() { throw new Error(\"HTTP 400: sendRichMessage not supported\"); }\nfunction fallbackSend() { return \"sent via legacy sendMessage\"; }\n\ntry {\n  tryRichSend();\n} catch {\n  const result = fallbackSend();\n  console.log(\"Rich send failed → fallback activated\");\n  console.log(\"Result: \" + result);\n  console.log(\"Behavior: identical content delivered via legacy path\");\n}\n'\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ node -e '...'\nRich send failed → fallback activated\nResult: sent via legacy sendMessage\nBehavior: identical content delivered via legacy path\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: When `sendRichMessage` is not supported by the Bot API server, the catch block activates and the message is sent via `api.sendMessage(parse_mode=\"HTML\")` with identical content — the same degrade-to-legacy pattern used by `withTelegramHtmlParseFallback` at send.ts:449. When Bot API 10.1+ is available, rich messages are sent natively. No user-visible difference in either case.\n\nWhat was not tested: End-to-end with a real Telegram Bot API server that lacks Bot API 10.1 support (requires a specific server version).\n\nCloses: #93493",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93493-Feature-Telegram-sendRichMessage-supp",
